                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14275796" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 19:45:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In 2.0 all the glyphs are missing. Of course the PDF is not really using UTF-8, because PDF doesn&apos;t support it - instead the fonts are Type0/TTF fonts with Identity-H encoding (i.e. raw GIDs).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14275912" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 20:45:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, I&apos;ve solved the main problem with 2.0. The file has a number of errors, the fonts use Identity-H encoding but are not embedded, the CID2GIDMap is missing, we expect to fallback to the ToUnicodeMap, but that is missing too. Broken fonts like these fall under an ambiguous part of the PDF spec:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The conforming reader shall select glyphs by translating characters from the encoding specified by the predefined CMap to one of the encodings in the TrueType font&apos;s &apos;cmap&apos; table. The means by which this is accomplished are implementation-dependent.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We try to emulate Acrobat&apos;s undocumented behaviour as much as possible, in the case it&apos;s not working as we were expecting a ToUnicodeMap to fall back to. The fix is to check if the ToUnicodeMap is missing, and if so, fall back to using an Identity encoding.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14275913" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 20:46:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1651484 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1651484&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1651484&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2599&quot; title=&quot;failure to render file with utf8 CID TT fonts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2599&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2599&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Assume Identity CID2GIDMap when there is no ToUnicode CMap to fallback to&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14275915" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 20:47:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This doesn&apos;t fix the barcode fonts, which render incorrect glyphs. Notably OS X Preview is not able to render the barcodes either, but Acrobat can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14275926" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 20:55:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The missing barcodes are due to the TTF font being embedded using the FontFile entry rather than FontFile2. This is invalid, but Acrobat handles it, so we will too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14275933" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 13 Jan 2015 21:00:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1651489 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jahewson&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jahewson&quot;&gt;jahewson&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1651489&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1651489&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2599&quot; title=&quot;failure to render file with utf8 CID TT fonts&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2599&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2599&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Check the FontFile entry when loading Type2 CIDFonts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
